[The report includes an interactive map showing the location of the event.

Since ASF penetrated Russia from Georgia in November 2007, the virus has become established in most of western Russia from south to north. Russia reported ASF as "resolved" on 16 Dec 2013, but a few days later had to report new outbreaks.

The Russian ASF OIE reporting history can be summarised as follows:

1. Initially started on 5 Nov 2007, Follow-up report No. 18 (Final report) declaring the disease "Resolved" submitted on 9 Jun 2009 (total 65 outbreaks)
2. Restarted on 11 Sep 2009, Follow-up report No. 110 (Final report) declaring the disease "Resolved" submitted on 16 Dec 2013 (total 302 outbreaks)
3. Restarted reporting on 1 Jan 2014, follow-up Rep. No. 1 10 Feb 2014 (2 outbreaks so far, status: "continuing")
4. Restarted reporting on 14 Jan 2014, follow-up Reps. No. 1-4: 27 Jan 2014, 3 Feb 2014, 5 Feb 2014, 11 Feb 2014 (5 outbreaks so far, status: "continuing")

At present, 2 separate epizootics in tandem are covered in 2 separate threads to the OIE. An explanation for that divided reporting would be helpful. - Mod.AS

A HealthMap/ProMED-mail map can be accessed at: http://healthmap.org/r/1MnT.]
